      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 60,
      "message": "Not sure but first may handle any errors which has been thrown upstream (decoding wire frame and protobuf). Then there is routing and Kafka. Then we handle only routing & sending errors. We do pass the flux to the KafkaSender (instead of mapping each item separately) so it might be the case that it doesn't handle errors as we expect.\n\nJust my guess.",
